This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel objective for a hybrid VAE-GAN framework to address the mode collapse and sample quality issues in generative modelling tasks. The paper also mentions the use of synthetic likelihood, which is a common technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as generative modelling is a common task in these fields. The use of GANs and VAEs also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) as these sub-categories often deal with neural networks and software development for machine learning applications.
